OL,3,C'Addicted': The teenagers who gave up
OL,4,Ctheir phones for a fortnight
OL,6,FSpeaking about the experiment, student
OL,7,FAnya said: "I know I'm addicted - I
OL,8,Fknow I am. It's just no one has ever
OL,9,Ftried to stop me."
OL,11,FWe also asked the pupils if they had
OL,12,Fcome across any harmful content while
OL,13,Fscrolling online, and their answers
OL,14,Franged from suicide to sexually
OL,15,Finappropriate material.
OL,17,FResearch by the Children's
OL,18,FCommissioner for England says almost
OL,19,Fthree-quarters of teenagers between 13
OL,20,Fand 17 have encountered one or more
OL,21,Fpotential harms online.
